  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nIs there any sort of coverage configuration file which can be fed to forge coverage? \r\nIf not, I think it would be great if it could read something like a `.solcover` file which is already used in the ecosystem for configuring files you might not want included as part of coverage (`skipFiles` property for example).\r\nI am aware you can do post-processing as stated here: https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/3147 but I think this would be a nice-to-have feature if it doesn't already exist.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
